==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phthongal
<hw>Phthon"gal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
voice.]</ety> <def>Formed into, or characterized by, voice; vocalized;
-- said of all the vowels and the semivowels, also of the vocal or
sonant consonants <xex>g</xex>, <xex>d</xex>, <xex>b</xex>,
<xex>l</xex>, <xex>r</xex>, <xex>v</xex>, <xex>z</xex>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phthongal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Phthongal
<hw>Phthon"gal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A vocalized element or
letter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

